ce:section.ce:para:
The membrane volume consists of two parts, one is the volume occupied by molecules of membrane constitutes, the other part is the unoccupied gaps between component molecules of the membrane, i.e., free volume (Vfree
                           ). The free volume is dispersed throughout the membrane and its existence allows the polymer chains could entangle. The free volume is of a concern as it is relative to the deformation of the membranes by water uptake and acid doping as well as the mechanical properties. The N2 sorption and desorption results of the composite membranes are shown in Table 1. The Vfree
                            of the composite membranes with CDs is obvious higher than that of the original membrane PVP-PES. This phenomenon is in good agreement with the microphase separation according to the AFM images (shown in Fig. 3).
